 LNG technology is a driver for Wärtsilä. This Wärtsilä gas valve unit (GVU) is a module located between the LNG storage system and the dual-fuel (DF) engine. It is used to regulate gas pressure and ensure a safe disconnect of the gas system.



All images are the intellectual property of Wärtsilä. They may be reproduced in conjunction with features, articles or other editorial with reference to Wärtsilä. In such publications image credit should be given as “Image courtesy of Wärtsilä Corporation – all rights reserved.”
